  "prompt": "What is achilles tendonitis?",
  "response": "Achilles tendonitis is an overuse injury that causes pain and inflammation in the Achilles tendon, the thick band of tissue that connects the calf muscles to the heel bone. Here are key details:\n\nSymptoms:\n- Pain along the back of the heel and above the heel\n- Stiffness and soreness, especially in the morning\n- Swelling around the tendon\n- Reduced range of motion\n- Thickening of the tendon\n\nCauses:\n- Repetitive stress on the tendon\n- Sudden increase in exercise intensity\n- Running or jumping activities\n- Tight calf muscles\n- Poor footwear\n- Age-related degeneration\n- Improper training techniques\n\nRisk factors:\n- Middle-aged athletes\n- Runners\n- People with flat feet or high arches\n- Sudden changes in exercise routine\n- Obesity\n- Certain medical conditions\n\nTreatment:\n- Rest and ice\n- Anti-inflammatory medications\n- Stretching exercises\n- Physical therapy\n- Orthotic devices\n- Compression bandages\n- Gradual return to activity\n- In severe cases, surgery might be required\n\nPrevention involves proper warm-up, gradual exercise progression, and using appropriate footwear.",
